## 1. Install the required libraries:
-> Make sure Python is installed and run:
pip install opencv-python numpy scikit-learn

## 2. Run the script:
-> Start the application with:
python finger_counting.py

## 3. Usage Instructions:
-> Allow the application to capture the background for 60 frames. During this time, avoid placing your hand in the ROI (Region of Interest).
-> Once the message "WAIT! GETTING BACKGROUND AVG." disappears, position your hand within the green box (ROI).
-> The program will segment the hand, count the number of extended fingers, and display the count on the video feed.
-> Press the Esc key to exit the application.
